  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tomorrow Now:  Education for South Sudan Girl&apos;s</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It&apos;s been 4-years since the outbreak of major conflict in South Sudan.  The country has the highest rate of children missing out on schooling in the world, 72% according to UNICEF in 2017.  Less than 1% of girls here will complete their secondary education.  HDC is a national NGO, working across the country to help those impacted by conflict &amp; displacement.  Through Tomorrow Now, we provide scholarships &amp; supports to girls to achieve their dream of obtaining an education.</narrative>
  </description>
